# CLAUDE.md

This file provides guidance to Claude Code (claude.ai/code) when working with code in this repository.

## Project

Obsidian vault implementing Luhmann's Zettelkasten. {{language}}-language notes. AI-assisted via Claude Code skills and OZC MCP server.

Core rule: one permanent note = one atomic idea. Value is in connections between notes, not notes alone.

## MCP Server (OZC)

The vault uses the `ozc` MCP server for all Zettelkasten operations. Tools are auto-discovered by Claude Code.

### Available MCP Tools

| Tool | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `zk_capture` | Create fleeting note |
| `zk_literature` | Create literature note from source |
| `zk_permanent` | Create permanent note with Luhmann ID |
| `zk_manage` | Edit/archive/delete by ID |
| `zk_promote` | Mark fleeting/literature as processed |
| `zk_finalize` | Quality-check permanent note, finalize if all checks pass |
| `zk_moc` | Create Map of Content — auto-pulls notes by tag cluster |
| `zk_project` | Create project note with objectives and tasks |
| `zk_backlinks` | Get incoming/outgoing links for a note |
| `zk_find_connections` | Find connection candidates |
| `zk_cluster_detect` | Find emerging themes |
| `zk_list` | List/filter notes |
| `zk_unprocessed` | Find unprocessed notes |
| `zk_orphans` | Find orphan notes |
| `zk_next_id` | Next Luhmann ID |
| `zk_find_by_id` | Resolve ID to path |
| `zk_tree` | Visualize Luhmann tree (full / subtree / context) |
| `zk_review` | Full vault health report |
| `zk_reindex` | Re-scan vault |
| `zk_status` | DB stats |

### Available Skills (Slash Commands)

`/zk:capture`, `/zk:literature`, `/zk:permanent`, `/zk:promote`, `/zk:manage`, `/zk:finalize`, `/zk:moc`, `/zk:project`, `/zk:review`, `/zk:daily`, `/zk:connect`, `/zk:reflect`

## Note folders & lifecycle

- `1-Fleeting/` — raw ideas (status: unprocessed → processed)
- `2-Literature/` — source notes (status: unprocessed → processed)
- `3-Permanent/` — atomic ideas with Luhmann IDs (status: draft → finalized)
- `4-MOC/` — Maps of Content (topic indexes)
- `5-Projects/` — active goals
- `Archive/` — cold storage

## Luhmann numbering

`zk_id` in permanent note frontmatter: `1, 2, 3` (top-level) → `1a, 1b` (branches) → `1a1, 1a2` (sub-branches). Alternating numbers/letters.

## Connection types (Ukrainian)

- **Підтримує** (Supports), **Суперечить** (Contradicts), **Розширює** (Extends), **Пов'язано** (Related)

## Language

All note content, section headers, and connection types in Ukrainian.
